So far today....

Emptied old entertainment center in the basement
Moved center
cleaned up home of dead mice behind entertainment center
re-ran cable lines in the basement so it reaches the new location for TV
drilled out lines needed for new location
cleaned and replaced ceiling tiles in basement room
checked out gas smell by the meter, it's coming from INSIDE the meter
         (I knew they broke it when they changed the meter... one should not strike a gas line/meter with a sledge hammer, but that what she did when she changed it to the "new" meter")  Yes, this is the third time since that I've reported gas odors by the meter.

straightened the food stores and re-arranged the shelves
2 loads of laundry
1 load of dishes
switched Katrina's old dresser out for a "new" one from grandpa that is bigger for her
including doing a 3/4 water change on Sabrina's fish tank and cleaning all parts because it sits on top of Katrina's dresser
cleaned attic entrance and moved dresser up there
re-arranged attic totes and found lots of old clothes that will fit Katrina
cleaned upstairs bathroom
removed shower head and cleaned it
cleaned living room
cleaned half of dining room
cleaned half of kitchen
dinner is cooking on the stove and in the oven.

Still need to clean my room

I picked up my mom after work went back to my house, had dinner then drove to the school for Zachary's Christmas Concert.  It was originally scheduled for Dec 16th but was rescheduled on Monday.  I had sent JoAnna a text letting her know it was rescheduled.

I dropped mom off and walked the parking lot fast.  Jo's car wasn't there at 6:55 and Zach was supposed to be there at 6:30.  I checked in the chorus room, nope, Zach wasn't there.

Waited until his portion of the concert and still no Zachary.

He's the ONLY fourth grader to not be in the concert.

What's the other name for a "domestic Terrorist"?


<lj-cut text="answer behind cut">
"Revolutionary"

I'm sure the British called the Colonists, "Domestic Terrorists".  We call them that.  They only remain terrorists until they succeed.  History is written by the winners after all.
</lj-cut>

I guess there was a lack of communication last night.  Before I even posted my update my Uncle had passed away.  Probably around 7:30 pm.  Services are at 9:30 am on Saturday.  At least he and my Aunt aren't suffering anymore.

Phone rang.
It was my mom.
My grandmother lost her battle with cancer this morning at 8:45 am.

Considering she was told she wouldn't live to see Christmas 2005...
Most of my life I hated her.
The past 10 years I finally got to know her.
She loved my kids.

I will miss her.

PS.  It's a testament to her sharp tongue and sense of humor that she should go on April Fools Day.  She married a man who later became a professional clown, whom she hated and loved till the day she died even though they divorced 35 years ago.

Source: IT humor
28 February 2007 


Once there were four engineers traveling in a car. While they were traveling to their destination the car stalled on them. 
Then the first engineer who was a mechanical engineer said, "don't worry its probably engine problems. I will just pop open the bonnet and take a look at the motor". 

Then the second engineer, who was an electrical engineer, said, "no, no ,no. It is an electrical problem. Just let me look at the fuse box and I will find the problem". 

The third engineer, who was a chemical engineer, said, "its just a problem with the fuel. Flush out all of the petrol and replace it with new clean petrol and you will see that the car will be fine." 

Then the three engineers looked at the fourth who was a computer engineer. And his response was... "Why don't we just get out of the car, shut all of the doors, and then open them again and get back in and start it!"

This is an example of why I hate News Channels. "Trial starts today for Ohio woman accused of killing her baby by putting in microwave" There are things that bother me now as a parent more than they used to. This being one of them. http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/15937773/

For those who haven't heard yet.  I'm home now.

Since Wednesday I've been at Ellis Hospital fighting what turned out to be Viral Meningitis with some extra twists.  At first I thought it was a bad case of the flu and the Nurse Practitioner I saw on Wed afternoon agreed, for the most part.  She ran some of her concerns by the on call doctor and then I was sent home with the understanding that if any of my symptoms changed, neck got stiff, fever came back, anything, I was to call the on-call doctor at once.

A couple hours later I called because my fever was up to 102 again and rising.  I waited what I thought was the 30 minutes for him to call back... it turned out to be two hours I had blacked out.  I got to the ER just before midnight only partially able to function on my own.  I had little good functionality with my eyes, neck, balance, ears, etc... basically everything from the shoulders up was a near dead zone from pain.  The nurses looked me over sent me to a room and I waited.  About 1 AM a nurse came in and gave me a shot of Toridal (sp?) which helped some symptoms after a few hours.  Then chest x-rays, CAT scans, and a couple blood cultures later it was decided I had to have a spinal tap done.

So, now I know that spinal fluid looks like vodka.

That confirmed what I had and off to admitting I went after 4 hours of immobilization.  Since then, I've been kept coherent through the wonderful world of drugs.  Mostly, Overdose levels of Motrin.  The pills I'm on now are only 4 times the dosage of what you get over the counter.

I've been treated for Bacterial Meningitis, sinus infections, the flu, and whatever else they could think of along the way.  My doctor finally got a full dose of my pain tolerance when he asked me to squeeze his hand as hard as my head hurt when the pain killers wore off.  His knuckles will take a few days to recover.  :)

When the pain gets bad enough that I can not see, hear, or keep my balance and I'm already on the IV pain killer.  I'm not joking when I say, IT HURTS!

We also found out that my health, even though I'm still really sick, is getting better and better.  With all of the stresses going on over the past few weeks my blood pressure, while high for me, has stayed in the lower range of normal.  Pulse rate was back down as well.  Only things to worry about are getting my weight back down and getting into shape, both involve time and exercise.

So, now I'm home.  I have a note from my doctor saying I'm not to return to work until Wednesday, but I think I'm going to fight him on that.  At least see if I can work what I can from home.

Remember to give thanks for everything you have.

We forget to do that as often as we should.

Quick update before work, since I can't tell Sabrina yet....

I checked the guinea pig cage this morning to make sure Midnight is doing okay.  I look into her little house and see a black guinea pig with a white stripe... Worried that something has happened to her I pick up her 'house'.

SomeONE happened to her!  We have three little ones in the cage with her now.  They are all mostly black like her mother, but one has a white nose on it.  They are cute but not what I need right now.  Oy.
Wow, this storm front coming through is making me a tad bit worried about the big butternut tree in the backyard...  It's taking a hard beating from this wind.

The Movie Of Your Life Is Film Noir
So what if you're a little nihilistic at times? Life with meaning is highly over-rated. Your best movie matches: Sin City, L. A. Confidential, Blade Runner
If Your Life Was a Movie, What Genre Would It Be?

Call me insensitive but at this point I don't care.  I've heard so much about this poor police officer's daughter who died.  Why?  Cause at 19 she was driving drunk.  Both she and her friend chose to commit suicide.  That's what getting drunk and behind the wheel of a car is.  I'm only thankful they didn't take anyone else with them.  Good riddance and get the pictures of the vehicle and funeral off the TV and move on to real news.

As JoAnna just told me in a voice mail "When it rains it pours.  I'm sorry but that is the way it seems to happen."

This was because I got the call at about 9 am that my dad was going in for emergency gall bladder surgery.  Emergency because the pain has been so bad he hasn't slept or eaten for 3 days.

And today I was told I couldn't have the time off to go to Tyler's Kindergarten Pre-screening results meeting.  *sigh*   just aint my day.
I received the call this morning.  My Aunt Diane Colleton lost her battle with Cancer early this morning.

I am a
Canna

What Flower
Are You?

Tyler came through his surgery fine.  He got through faster than they thought it would take to do both eyes.  Then he shook off the anethesia in 20 minutes instead of the 1-2 hours they thought it would take.

All in all, it was a traumatic experience... no matter what anyone says... I still feel like someone put me in an emotional blender and hit "Frappe"
Tomorrow morning... at 10:30 am they will be starting to cut into Tyler...  Wish me luck.  This would be a hell of a lot easier to survive if there were going to be someone there I could lean on.

Okay.  Went in for the follow up appointment today.  The outcome is "You're not great, but you're not bad either."  So, there's been improvement.  I'm not on the "permanently disabled" list at the moment, but I'm definately on the "things will not be the same" list.

My sphere is Guardian (Person of great Love and Altruism), and my class is Champion (Self-Righteous and Confident).

I am a Hero.

You are true heroic material. You find great motivation in the things you love, and great inspiration in your sense of self-confidence, and your excellence. Once you get your mind set on a goal, you are nearly unstoppable, and given enough time, you will meet it.

What kind of Warrior are you?

"If you read this, if your eyes are passing over this right now, even if we don't speak often, please post a comment with a memory of you and me. It can be anything you want -- good or bad. When you're finished, post this little paragraph on your blog and be surprised (or mortified) about what people remember about you."

Update on my mother, her hemoglobin had gotten down to 6.  Which basically means her blood couldn't carry enough oxygen to her system to support brain functions.  Hence the dementia that set in yesterday.  More information as it comes in... they have her scheduled for screening for stomach cancer next.
I just got the phone call from my dad.  My mother is on her way to the ER in the ambulance.

Is it a bad thing that I'm taking the prescribed amount of Lortab and Advil and am still feeling pain?  I know I've been told not to worry about the occasional chest pains and the continual throbbing I'm feeling but this is bugging me.  Especially since I'm now going from getting up and being light headed cause my blood pressure is too low to walking up a flight of stairs and having half of me lit up in pain.  Gah.

Just shoot me now.  The life insurance is paid up.

Well, it happened today...

Quote of the night...
"I don't want to just rain on your parade, I want to blow up the floats!"

My mom is going to be getting her transfusion tonight... they have put her on more medicines to control the reactions and they also spent 48 hours doing more exacting cross matching on her blood in Syracuse before shipping it.  Instead of just typing they did a lot more than that.

I have my fingers crossed.  Things are going well with my job so my personal life is crap.  Big surprise.  *sigh*

Okay... with all of the exercise I've been getting at work, along with the fact that I've been working to control (not ignore) my eating, I've lost 10 pounds in 2 weeks.  I'm actually trying to curb some of that.  I don't want to lose it too fast or I'm going to not be able to keep it off.

DAMN!  I was going to go see "Pirates II" again tonight.  It's only $3.50 at the local theater.  Nope... Can't do that.

They are now showing "The Devil Wears Prada" and I'm just not in the mood for that one tonight.

Well, the friggin county denied my application for Food Stamps and Temporary Assistance on a shit hole of a reason.

"Because you didn't interview on the day you applied and we offered to do so..."

Um... NO!!!  When I applied, the woman behind the desk said, "We're running at least 8-10 days behind on interviews.  We'll let you know when you're appointment is."

Now, a month later, after I've tried calling them shitloads of times at the number they gave me and ALWAYS getting a message of "We're sorry but this Mailbox is FULL" they deny me saying I didn't try.

And of course, the number they gave for calling to get a conference no one is ANSWERING!!!

I called from my cell and left it on speakerphone.  It rang for more than an HOUR without anyone picking up.

I'm so pissed right now.

Okay, the final word on things is that I start work on Monday morning 8 am.  I got the shift I wanted as well!

Fred apparently asked for that shift without talking to me since he has kids too.  :)

For once it is raining good things.

New Horizons CLC out of Albany just emailed me looking for a phone interview for a Teaching Position at the Albany office.

To bad they waited this long.  Last time I was searching for work and interviewed there they offered me a whole $8/hr to start and I had to take a bunch of certifications from them using their personal loans to do it.  Basically indentured servitude from the way they talked.  Not something I could do with kids.
